<p>Use Amakode to transcode music between formats when copying files to your media player.</p>

<p>Home page: <a href="http://www.tarind.com/amakode.html">http://www.tarind.com/amakode.html</a></p>

<p>Feedback at kde-apps: <a href="http://www.kde-apps.org/content/show.php/Amakode?content=48218">http://www.kde-apps.org/content/show.php/Amakode?content=48218</a>

<p>Amakode it is written in Python. It uses external programs to perform the grunt work
so you may also need to install one or more of following using your package manager:</p>

<ul>
<li><b>tagpy</b> library - to preserve tags. This is in the python-tagpy package.</li>
<li><b>ogg123</b> - if you want to decode ogg</li>
<li><b>mpg123</b> - if you want decode mp3</li>
<li><b>mplayer</b> - if you want to decode mp4</li>
<li><b>flac</b> - if you want to decode flac</li>
<li><b>oggenc</b> - if you want to encode ogg</li>
<li><b>lame</b> - if you want to encode mp3</li>
<li><b>faac</b> - if you want to encode mp4</li>
</ul>


